Preheat your #oven to 200°C. Halve the @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125}. Halve the @Ciabatta{1} (as if you were making a sandwich) and chop into 2cm chunks. Pop them both on a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Red Onion{1}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Cut the @Halloumi{250} into three slices per person. Place the halloumi slices in a small bowl of cold water and leave to soak. Drain and rinse the @Lentils{1} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan on medium heat and add the red onion. Season with @salt{} and cook, stirring occasionally, until really soft, ~{5-7%minutes}. Add the @Balsamic Vinegar{12}, pop a lid on and turn the heat down to low. Cook until caramelised, stirring occasionally, ~{3-4%minutes}. Once cooked, stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @Water{75} and stir in the @Vegetable Stock Powder{1}. Bring to the boil and simmer until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the lentils. Bring to the boil and cook the lentils until piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if you feel it needs it.

While everything cooks, bake the tomatoes and ciabatta in your #oven until the croutons are golden and the tomatoes softened, ~{8-10%minutes}. Once cooked remove from the oven and set aside. Once the lentils are piping hot, add in the @Baby Spinach{100} a handful at a time and cook until wilted, ~{1-2%minutes}. When wilted, pop a lid on and remove from the heat. Set aside.

While the spinach wilts, put a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add a drizzle of @oil{}. Once the oil is hot, add the @Chorizo{90} and stir fry until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from the pan to a #bowl{}, pop back on a medium high heat and add a drizzle of @oil{} if needed. Once the oil is hot, lay in the halloumi slices. Fry until golden, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side, then remove the pan from the heat.

Stir the tomatoes, chorizo and croutons into the lentils, taste and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if you feel it needs it. Serve the lentils in #bowls{} with the halloumi slices on top. Enjoy!

> MOD Step 5: If you've added chorizo to your meal, pop your pan on the heat as instructed but before you fry the halloumi, add the chorizo and stir fry until it starts to brown, 3-4 mins. Remove the chorizo from the pan to a bowl. Pop the pan back on a medium high heat and add a drizzle of oil. Cook the halloumi as instructed.

> Step 6 MOD: If you added chorizo to your meal, stir it through the lentils when you stir through the tomatoes.